{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' post-gen-interventions/com.h2database_h2_2.1.210.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Post-generation intervention report\n\nLibrary: com.h2database:h2:2.1.210\nStage: metadata_fix_failed\n\n## Summary\n\nThe metadata-fix log and native test output did not show a remaining `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for the failing tests. The failures were caused by generated tests that exercised runtime Java compilation, isolated `URLClassLoader` loading, image-time H2 property initialization, and test-order side effects around `DriverManager`, not by missing reachability metadata.\n\nI removed or narrowed only the generated tests that triggered those unsupported/native-image-specific paths. I did not modify metadata files.\n\n## Failure root causes and intervention\n\n- `SourceCompilerTest.compilesWithJavaxToolsCompilerAndDiscoversStaticMethod()` and `SourceCompilerTest.compilesWithLegacySunJavacAndDiscoversStaticMethod()` failed with `ClassNotFoundException` for `h2.generated.*` classes. These tests depend on compiling and loading new Java classes at native-image runtime, which is not reachability metadata that can be represented by the repository metadata schema. Removed `SourceCompilerTest.java`.\n- `TriggerObjectTest.compilesTriggerSourceAndInvokesFactoryMethod()` failed while H2 tried to compile trigger source into `org.h2.dynamic.trigger.SOURCE_TRIGGER`. This is the same runtime-source-compilation limitation, not missing reflection metadata. Removed only that generated test method and its `SourceTrigger` test fixture, while preserving the passing trigger-class registration test.\n- `UpgradeTest.loadsAndUnloadsLegacyDriverWithUpgradeTool()` failed because H2's upgrade path tried to load an external legacy H2 driver through dynamic class loading, but the native image resolved/unloaded the wrong driver. This also caused downstream `No suitable driver` failures in `UserAggregateTest` and `ValueToObjectConverterTest` by deregistering the active H2 driver. Removed `UpgradeTest.java` and the legacy-H2 test-only Gradle/resource wiring.\n- `MemoryUnmapperTest.unmapUsesLegacyCleanerFallbackWhenUnsafeIsUnavailable()` failed because it used a custom `URLClassLoader` to reload H2 classes while hiding `sun.misc.Unsafe`; the native image did not reproduce the JVM-only loader isolation behavior. Removed only that generated fallback test and its test fixtures, while preserving the direct buffer/heap buffer `MemoryUnmapper` coverage.\n- `JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test` failed because `SysProperties.USE_THREAD_CONTEXT_CLASS_LOADER` was frozen as `false` in the native image despite the test-only JVM system property. That is an image-initialization/platform behavior issue, not missing reachability metadata. Removed `JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test.java`.\n\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\n\nThe remaining H2 generated tests exercise ordinary reflection, resource, serialization, JDBC, ICU, file-system, authentication, trigger-class, aggregate, and object-conversion paths that are valid reachability-metadata coverage. After removing the unsupported generated tests, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.h2database:h2:2.1.210` passed with `32 tests successful` and `0 tests failed`, confirming that the preserved support is useful and no longer blocked by non-metadata failures.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
